South Africa is on level three lockdown and most people are returning to work. But things are a little different now. Mandatory social distancing and masks are a part of life. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -South Africa is on level three lockdown and most people are returning to work but things are a little different now. Mandatory social distancing and masks are a part of life. Public transport is hoping to adapt to the new normal using camera technology to enhance safety on public buses while reducing the spread of COVID-19 Compliance to lockdown regulations has been preached by Transport Minister, Fikile Mbalula. Lockdown level 3: Taxis back on the road full-time With more people commuting to work on level three public transport needs to adapt with the times. Putco says the move to install the cameras is to assess passenger behavior. Netstar equipped over 1,400 buses with these cameras. COVID-19 regulations surveillance will remain enforced until the pandemic is over. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.